      "id": "document:ADR-011-prose-quality-stop-slop.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Prose quality is governed harness-wide by a vendored stop-slop skill, with a condensed always-on chat convention",
      "filePath": "ADR-011-prose-quality-stop-slop.md",
      "summary": "Governs prose quality harness-wide via a vendored stop-slop skill plus a condensed always-on chat convention, rather than a hook/gate or intake-first mechanism.",
      "tags": [
        "prose-quality",
        "stop-slop",
        "skill",
        "convention"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-012-agents-execute-skills-hold-knowledge.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Agents execute, skills hold knowledge; agent definitions point to a skill as single source of truth",
      "filePath": "ADR-012-agents-execute-skills-hold-knowledge.md",
      "summary": "Separates concerns so agents execute while skills hold knowledge, with agent definitions pointing to a skill as single source of truth rather than baking rules into the prompt.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "skills",
        "single-source-of-truth",
        "separation-of-concerns"
      ],
      "complexity": "simple"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-013-floor-on-demand-backbone.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Session-lifecycle backbone — always-on automatic floor plus on-demand commands; no close ritual",
      "filePath": "ADR-013-floor-on-demand-backbone.md",
      "summary": "Defines the session-lifecycle backbone as an always-on automatic floor plus on-demand commands with no close ritual; supersedes ADR-008 and amends ADR-004/005/006/007.",
      "tags": [
        "session-lifecycle",
        "floor",
        "on-demand",
        "hooks",
        "supersedes"
      ],
      "complexity": "complex"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-014-quality-first-over-leanness.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Quality first — size and leanness are backstops, never the objective",
      "filePath": "ADR-014-quality-first-over-leanness.md",
      "summary": "Reframes quality as the objective with size/leanness only as backstops; amends ADR-007 (token budget as soft ceiling) and ADR-008 (gate optimizes for quality).",
      "tags": [
        "quality-first",
        "leanness",
        "principle",
        "amends"
      ],
      "complexity": "complex"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-015-agent-skill-load-rule-methodology-vs-spawn-target.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Agents that front a skill load it only when they run the skill to completion; spawn-target agents must not",
      "filePath": "ADR-015-agent-skill-load-rule-methodology-vs-spawn-target.md",
      "summary": "Refines ADR-012: an agent loads its fronting skill only when it runs that skill to completion; spawn-target agents (e.g. doubt-reviewer) must not load the spawning skill.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "skills",
        "load-rule",
        "spawn-target"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-016-confident-core-capability-domains.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Pre-build a bounded confident-core of capability domains; intake gate governs the rest",
      "filePath": "ADR-016-confident-core-capability-domains.md",
      "summary": "Pre-builds a bounded confident-core of five capability domains while the intake gate governs the rest; amends ADR-008 by moving languages from reactive to build-now.",
      "tags": [
        "capability-domains",
        "confident-core",
        "intake-gate",
        "amends"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-017-agent-design-contract.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Main session orchestrates; agents are scoped specialists on a lean ECC-style contract",
      "filePath": "ADR-017-agent-design-contract.md",
      "summary": "Keeps the main session as orchestrator and agents as scoped specialists on a lean ECC-style contract, rejecting a per-language/per-domain agent matrix and deferring per-agent model pinning.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "orchestration",
        "design-contract",
        "scoped-specialists"
      ],
      "complexity": "complex"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-018-agent-authoring-method.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Authoring method — caller-agnostic skill loaded by a lean executor; eval-first disciplines, scoped",
      "filePath": "ADR-018-agent-authoring-method.md",
      "summary": "Sets the agent authoring method: a caller-agnostic skill loaded by a lean executor, with eval-first disciplines scoped rather than reconstructing review/dev substance or adopting ECC internals wholesale.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "authoring-method",
        "skill",
        "eval-first"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-019-agent-evaluation-model.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Evaluation — agent-self-evaluation as advisory per-task done-condition check; formal eval suites stay reactive; gates unchanged",
      "filePath": "ADR-019-agent-evaluation-model.md",
      "summary": "Adopts agent-self-evaluation as an advisory per-task done-condition check, keeps formal eval suites reactive, and leaves promotion gates unchanged.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "evaluation",
        "advisory",
        "self-evaluation"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    },
    {
      "id": "document:ADR-020-agent-debugging-model.md",
      "type": "document",
      "name": "Debugging — adopt the introspection self-debug loop; scope the architecture audit to owned layers; diagnostic, never a gate",
      "filePath": "ADR-020-agent-debugging-model.md",
      "summary": "Adopts an introspection self-debug loop and scopes the architecture audit to owned layers, keeping it diagnostic and never a gate.",
      "tags": [
        "agents",
        "debugging",
        "introspection",
        "diagnostic"
      ],
      "complexity": "moderate"
    }
